If we eat a lot,

95
00:05:13,020 --> 00:05:15,560
we'll have to make a bad soba that we can never eat again.

96
00:05:20,880 --> 00:05:22,360
Are you a customer?

97
00:05:23,040 --> 00:05:24,560
I was going to say that.

98
00:05:25,160 --> 00:05:26,540
Thank you very much.

99
00:05:26,860 --> 00:05:27,800
What's wrong?

100
00:05:28,380 --> 00:05:30,760
Actually, you are the fifth customer.

101
00:05:31,260 --> 00:05:32,640
The fifth customer today?

102
00:05:32,660 --> 00:05:33,440
Well, I guess that's it.

103
00:05:33,920 --> 00:05:36,380
No, it's the fifth since the restaurant started.

104
00:05:37,460 --> 00:05:37,920
What?

105
00:05:38,680 --> 00:05:39,500
Wait a minute!

106
00:05:40,220 --> 00:05:41,320
When did the restaurant start?

107
00:05:41,320 --> 00:05:42,760
Three years ago.

108
00:05:42,980 --> 00:05:44,400
Three years ago?

109
00:05:45,940 --> 00:05:47,480
I'll make it right away.

110
00:05:47,840 --> 00:05:48,800
What should I do?

111
00:05:49,260 --> 00:05:50,800
Actually, I suddenly feel a little hungry.

112
00:05:52,940 --> 00:05:56,020
Senior, I feel sorry for you.

113
00:05:56,320 --> 00:05:57,040
Let's eat it.

114
00:05:57,620 --> 00:05:59,440
What should we do if we eat soba here and really feel hungry?

115
00:06:01,860 --> 00:06:02,560
If something happens,

116
00:06:02,860 --> 00:06:04,460
we'll do something with Nakagawa Zaibatsu's medical team.

117
00:06:08,340 --> 00:06:10,020
Let's be the fifth customer.

118
00:06:10,020 --> 00:06:10,640
Please.

119
00:06:12,380 --> 00:06:13,560
I understand.

120
00:06:14,260 --> 00:06:15,460
I'll be the fifth victim.

121
00:06:18,360 --> 00:06:25,560
Thank you for waiting.

122
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:28,600
It's a bad soba.

123
00:06:28,980 --> 00:06:30,460
Let's eat it quickly and go back to the delivery.

124
00:06:32,180 --> 00:06:32,820
What?

125
00:06:35,580 --> 00:06:36,880
Don't look at me!

126
00:06:37,280 --> 00:06:38,500
I'm sorry.

127
00:06:38,720 --> 00:06:40,000
The customer's reaction is a little...

128
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:40,880
You're worried about the soba, aren't you?

129
00:06:41,460 --> 00:06:41,880
Yes.

130
00:06:42,260 --> 00:06:43,560
I'll tell you after I finish eating.

131
00:06:44,440 --> 00:06:45,500
So go over there while I'm eating.

132
00:06:47,400 --> 00:06:47,820
Yes.

133
00:06:52,440 --> 00:06:53,560
It's a soba with no weirdness.

134
00:06:54,440 --> 00:06:55,860
It's not that bad that you can't eat it.

135
00:06:58,740 --> 00:07:01,400
What's this?

136
00:07:01,960 --> 00:07:03,140
What's wrong, Nakagawa?

137
00:07:03,480 --> 00:07:05,100
Master, I have something to ask you.

138
00:07:05,480 --> 00:07:06,680
Yes, what is it?

139
00:07:07,380 --> 00:07:09,860
Is this soba made from the soba flour made at Yamada Farm?

140
00:07:11,480 --> 00:07:12,380
Yes, it is.

141
00:07:13,180 --> 00:07:15,180
What's Yamada Farm?

142
00:07:15,920 --> 00:07:16,700
You know it.

143
00:07:17,220 --> 00:07:18,300
It's the farm of the soba maker,

144
00:07:19,080 --> 00:07:20,180
Dengoro Yamada.

145
00:07:23,780 --> 00:07:26,260
It's said that the soba made here is the best in Japan.

146
00:07:27,260 --> 00:07:28,920
It's difficult to get,

147
00:07:28,920 --> 00:07:30,860
so even the Nakagawa group's cooking department

148
00:07:30,860 --> 00:07:32,540
uses it only in a few shops.

149
00:07:33,900 --> 00:07:36,420
I've known the Yamada grandpa for a long time,

150
00:07:37,600 --> 00:07:39,480
so I've been using it cheaply at home.

151
00:07:40,240 --> 00:07:41,060
I knew it.

152
00:07:41,680 --> 00:07:42,560
And the soba made from the soba broth,

153
00:07:44,400 --> 00:07:45,800
isn't it the one made by Sato Jozo?

154
00:07:47,440 --> 00:07:47,920
Yes.

155
00:07:48,620 --> 00:07:52,240
Sato Jozo has been making handmade soba for years.

156
00:07:52,480 --> 00:07:53,200
It's said to be the birthplace of soba.

157
00:07:54,360 --> 00:07:56,340
It's a traditional taste of Kishu.

158
00:07:57,020 --> 00:08:00,520
The soba made here is called "soba in soba".

159
00:08:01,200 --> 00:08:02,520
No, it's called "soba".

160
00:08:02,520 --> 00:08:02,880
It's not just soba.

161
00:08:02,960 --> 00:08:05,020
It's also called "katsuobushi" and "konbu".

162
00:08:05,020 --> 00:08:06,460
It's a must-have for this rich broth.

163
00:08:09,020 --> 00:08:10,640
The green onions are well-cooked,

164
00:08:10,800 --> 00:08:12,020
and it's a great, glossy dish.

165
00:08:13,080 --> 00:08:14,460
And the chili peppers,

166
00:08:14,500 --> 00:08:16,900
the 7 flavors bring out the perfect harmony.

167
00:08:18,160 --> 00:08:19,400
The spiciness is just right,

168
00:08:19,820 --> 00:08:21,740
and it's a very well-chosen ingredient.

169
00:08:23,480 --> 00:08:25,920
Hey, hey, why do you use such a great ingredient

170
00:08:25,920 --> 00:08:27,560
to make only ordinary soba?

171
00:08:28,540 --> 00:08:29,240
Ordinary?

172
00:08:29,240 --> 00:08:31,400
Senior, please have a look at your bowl.

173
00:08:32,880 --> 00:08:34,120
When did you find it?

174
00:08:34,520 --> 00:08:35,580
This is what it means to be delicious.

175
00:08:37,500 --> 00:08:39,360
It goes into your body naturally.

176
00:08:41,820 --> 00:08:43,420
Old man, that's for you!

177
00:08:43,560 --> 00:08:44,200
One more, please!

178
00:08:44,420 --> 00:08:44,740
Yes!

179
00:08:47,160 --> 00:08:49,340
It is true that it tastes good when you chew it.

180
00:08:51,460 --> 00:08:52,040
Right?

181
00:08:52,320 --> 00:08:53,460
You're putting out such a great flavor.

182
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:55,420
You should promote it more!

183
00:08:55,600 --> 00:08:57,740
I'm not good at making flashy things.

184
00:08:58,100 --> 00:08:58,860
But even so,

185
00:08:58,860 --> 00:08:59,500
It's strange to think about it.

186
00:08:59,980 --> 00:09:02,900
If it tastes like this, it seems like it's going to attract customers.

187
00:09:03,480 --> 00:09:06,580
But there's a deep reason for it not to attract customers.

188
00:09:06,820 --> 00:09:07,800
Deep reason?

189
00:09:08,200 --> 00:09:10,440
Three years ago, I won't forget.

190
00:09:11,440 --> 00:09:14,920
On a day when the snow was falling, this store opened.

191
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:21,860
I was nervous, waiting for the first customer.

192
00:09:23,060 --> 00:09:24,220
Then...

193
00:09:26,560 --> 00:09:26,880
Sorry.

194
00:09:30,160 --> 00:09:31,720
What? You're Mr. Oomaeda?

195
00:09:32,180 --> 00:09:34,800
You're Mr. Oomaeda. Did you come here to eat?

196
00:09:35,300 --> 00:09:37,100
No, I came to borrow the bathroom.

197
00:09:40,120 --> 00:09:42,040
So this was a soba restaurant.

198
00:09:42,820 --> 00:09:44,060
I didn't realize it was so ordinary.

199
00:09:45,660 --> 00:09:47,400
But it's just right. Let's have lunch here.

200
00:09:48,640 --> 00:09:50,340
Yes, I'll make it right away.

201
00:09:51,660 --> 00:09:55,380
It was my first customer, so I made it with my own hands.

202
00:09:56,960 --> 00:09:57,600
Here you go.

203
00:09:59,200 --> 00:09:59,900
Thank you.

204
00:10:21,380 --> 00:10:22,480
How was it?

205
00:10:23,100 --> 00:10:24,420
It's just an ordinary taste.

206
00:10:24,620 --> 00:10:27,060
Is that so?

207
00:10:30,420 --> 00:10:34,120
Oh, it will be 700 yen, but...

208
00:10:35,840 --> 00:10:39,160
Sir, I don't think you know me.

209
00:10:40,060 --> 00:10:43,260
I'm Chogoro Omaeda, a food critic.

210
00:10:44,400 --> 00:10:48,040
Yes, so it will be 700 yen for a bowl of kakesoba.

211
00:10:48,220 --> 00:10:52,040
I'm Chogoro Omaeda, a food critic from Nippon-ishi!

212
00:10:52,860 --> 00:10:56,020
So, 700 yen for a bowl of kakesoba.

213
00:10:56,020 --> 00:10:58,580
I said I'm Omaeda!

214
00:11:00,120 --> 00:11:02,600
So, 700 yen for a bowl of kakesoba.

215
00:11:02,600 --> 00:11:04,480
I said I'm Omaeda!

216
00:11:05,320 --> 00:11:06,840
700 yen...

217
00:11:06,840 --> 00:11:09,940
I'm sorry, but I don't have any cash.

218
00:11:10,560 --> 00:11:12,460
I'll have to pay you back later.

219
00:11:12,880 --> 00:11:15,560
I'm sure it'll be 20,000 or 30,000 yen.

220
00:11:17,400 --> 00:11:19,280
Thank you very much.

221
00:11:20,720 --> 00:11:22,620
Sir, what's the name of this shop?

222
00:11:23,260 --> 00:11:24,400
Tanaka Soba.

223
00:11:26,020 --> 00:11:27,380
Tanaka Soba.

224
00:11:28,320 --> 00:11:29,560
I'll remember that.

225
00:11:32,260 --> 00:11:36,980
In the end, the full-year room was a complete fake.

226
00:11:37,900 --> 00:11:39,040
What a sad story.

227
00:11:39,560 --> 00:11:41,480
I was surprised a week later.

228
00:11:41,960 --> 00:11:43,120
They were so mean to our shop.

229
00:11:46,640 --> 00:11:48,360
It's not a human's fault.

230
00:11:49,020 --> 00:11:51,700
Even if the world forgives me, I won't forgive it.

231
00:11:52,480 --> 00:11:53,220
-7 times.

232
00:11:53,500 --> 00:11:54,280
That's terrible.

233
00:11:54,280 --> 00:11:55,580
Don't put this on display.

234
00:11:56,220 --> 00:11:58,320
But our shop is introduced.

235
00:11:59,340 --> 00:12:00,580
It's just a negative image.

236
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:03,840
It's a terrible article.

237
00:12:04,080 --> 00:12:05,320
It's full of criticism.

238
00:12:06,660 --> 00:12:10,240
